title: Big Thicket Lake Estates, Texas
text:
Big Thicket Lake Estates is a <a href="census-designated%20place">census-designated place</a> (CDP) in <a href="Polk%20County%2C%20Texas">Polk</a> and <a href="Liberty%20County%2C%20Texas">Liberty</a> counties, <a href="Texas">Texas</a>, United States. This was a new CDP for the <a href="United%20States%20Census%202010">2010 census</a>, with a population of 742.
Geography.
Big Thicket Lake Estates is located along the southern border of Polk County and the northern border of Liberty County at (30.487388, -94.767885). The CDP has a total area of , of which are land and , or 7.39%, are water. It is a residential community built around several artificial lakes, the largest of which is Bear Foot Lake, a reservoir built on Mill Creek, a tributary of Menard Creek and then the <a href="Trinity%20River%20%28Texas%29">Trinity River</a>.
<a href="Texas%20State%20Highway%20146">Texas State Highway 146</a> forms the western edge of the community. The highway leads north to <a href="Livingston%2C%20Texas">Livingston</a> and south to <a href="Liberty%2C%20Texas">Liberty</a>.
Education.
Sections in Polk County are divided between the <a href="Big%20Sandy%20Independent%20School%20District%20%28Polk%20County%2C%20Texas%29">Big Sandy Independent School District</a> and the <a href="Livingston%20Independent%20School%20District">Livingston Independent School District</a>. Parts in Liberty County are in the <a href="Hardin%20Independent%20School%20District">Hardin Independent School District</a>.
